  Abu Dhabi Islamic Bank  PJSC rose to
a four-month high as the  United Arab Emirates â€™ second-biggest
bank complying with shariah rules posted fourth-quarter profit.  The shares gained 2.6 percent to 3.19 dirhams, the highest
intraday level since Oct. 21, at 10:20 a.m. in Abu Dhabi.  Net income was 114.1 million dirhams ($31 million) after a
loss of 623.3 million dirhams in the year-earlier period. Credit
provisions and impairments dropped 68 percent, while income from
fees and commissions increased 43 percent and net revenue from
funding activities rose 26 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
